  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides designer functionality for user controls.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 There is no developer advantage to creating your own designer derived from <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.UserControlDesigner>. To enhance the design-time experience for a custom control, derive your control from <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.CompositeControl> and your designer from <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.CompositeControlDesigner>. In that case, you would not use an .ascx file for your ASP.NET markup.  
  
 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
